				\begin{document}$$\times$$\end{document} 108 CFU/mL) and then incubated at 37 °C for 24 h. The bacterial growth was measured as turbidity with a Multiskan™ GO Microplate Spectrophotometer at an OD of 600 nm. The results were then analyzed based on a two-sample student’s t-test to determine statistical differences between the treatments and our positive control grown without the presence of AuNPs.
